Commit Message: Initial commit of Kubrick, director of AWS instances.
Initial commit
Renames some files and constants
Working version of kubrick
Adds functions for storing a file in an s3 bucket
Adds Ubuntu specific mixins
Install Ubuntu packages all at once
Fixes race condition when first creating AWS instance
Adds a warn only option to the server run command
Always attempt to update the version of distribute before pip installing
Adds shell option when adding non root user
Use config variable for key file
Restructures package, adds installer, and tests
Adds some unit tests and a host_string property on AWSServers
Add root user now takes a home dir option

Adds additional files necessary to make this a complete package

Adds requirements to setup.py, makes tests run without having to
install the package, adds most basic documentation, and a makefile for
running tests and installing.
Makes the apt-get update/upgrade part fault tolerant
Updates Ubuntu AMI to 12.10
Adds a turn off disk check method
Adds method to uncomment ubuntu repositories
Refactor duplicated settings code into a decorator
Adds method to freeze apt sources list on ubuntu machines
